      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Tricky race to start the day. SNAP DECISION (4) deep into the preparation and given the good grounding for this. Returned a solid set of closing splits with an eye catching sixth over 1600m at Wagga. Can race closer from the good draw and return to winning form. STORMZINO (8) Sydney-trained mare desperate to shed her Maiden tag at start nine. Kept safe in betting with a fighting second in the small field over 2100m at Beaumont (Newcastle). Ready to win and has solid prospects. SON O' WAR (9) placed at the trip and will relish the weight drop after running on late over the shorter trips. On the quick backup and not without each way claims. TAVIJEWEL (5) consistent gelding building a sound record over this distance range. Went back from the wide draw and made up a stack of ground over the final 250m to secure second over 2120m at this track. Sure to be thereabouts. The chances don't end there.",
